# importing the required library
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
 
    
from matplotlib import pyplot


# a4_dims = (11.7, 8.27)
# fig, ax = pyplot.subplots(figsize=a4_dims)    
plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))

sns.set_style('darkgrid')

l = sns.barplot(x = "found in n RDs", y = "Term", data = top_20_HPO, palette = 'hls')

for p in l.patches:
    width = p.get_width()
    plt.text(30+p.get_width(), p.get_y()+0.55*p.get_height(),
             '{:1.2f}'.format(width),
             ha='center', va='center')

plt.xlabel("Number of rare diseases associated", size=14)
plt.ylabel("HPOs", size=14) 

plt.show()

Most common HPOs per Frequency class¶

In [18]:
HPO["count"] = 1
HPO_term_freq_count = HPO.groupby(["HPO_term", "Frequency_class"], as_index=False)["count"].sum()
HPO_freq_c1_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Obligate (100%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
HPO_freq_c2_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Very frequent (99-80%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
HPO_freq_c3_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Frequent (79-30%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
HPO_freq_c4_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Occasional (29-5%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
HPO_freq_c5_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Very rare (<4-1%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
HPO_freq_c6_top50 = HPO_term_freq_count[HPO_term_freq_count["Frequency_class"]  == 'Excluded (0%)'].sort_values(by=['count'], ascending=False).head(50)
